WEBVTT

C01
00:00:03.670 --> 00:00:09.319
Open Lab, choose New agent, and start the guided creation flow.

C02
00:00:09.039 --> 00:00:18.125
Choose From prompt to describe the Agent directly, or From chats to include examples of the work it should handle.

C04
00:00:17.845 --> 00:00:26.712
For this Account Health Agent, state its purpose and select three chats that show the facts, risks, and answer format it should use.

C06
00:00:26.432 --> 00:00:34.991
The first button only opens this review. Nothing is shared until you approve the selected chats on this screen.

C07
00:00:34.711 --> 00:00:43.797
Check the Agent's purpose, expected behavior, supporting chats, and the checks OpenPond will run before continuing to its plan.

C08
00:00:43.517 --> 00:00:49.434
The right side panel asks how the Agent should prioritize conflicting account risks.

C09
00:00:49.154 --> 00:00:57.931
Review the proposed name, chat behavior, direct actions, and outputs, then confirm or edit the plan.

C10
00:00:57.651 --> 00:01:08.167
OpenPond checks the Agent against the Account Health examples, so saving it depends on verified behavior instead of a plausible-looking draft.

C11
00:01:07.887 --> 00:01:14.568
After the checks pass, the Agent is saved to your Profile and is ready to use.

C12
00:01:14.288 --> 00:01:20.791
The Agent page shows its purpose, chat entrypoint, and runnable account actions.
